OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1776366671
OL,3,CMinister urges Home Office to help
OL,4,Cpassengers 'wrongly denied boarding'
OL,6,FA senior Government of Jersey
OL,7,Fpolitician is urging the UK Home
OL,8,FOffice to help passengers who she says
OL,9,Fare being "wrongly denied boarding" on
OL,10,Fsome international flights.
OL,12,FDeputy Mary Le Hegarat, the island's
OL,13,FJustice and Home Affairs Minister, has
OL,14,Fwritten to her counterparts in Britain
OL,15,Fto "express concern" and ask for their
OL,16,Fassistance.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/7
